{"url": "http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2016/06/14/orlando-shooting-vigil-london-vogue-battle_n_10458262.html", "date": "2016-06-14", "content": "Thousands poured into London's Soho neighborhood on Monday to pay tribute to the 49 people slain in the shooting at a gay nightclub in Orlando, Florida, this past weekend.\nBars stopped serving at 6:00 p.m. local time to allow for a moment of silence, which was followed by applause and cheering. Hundreds of balloons were released into the sky, Reuters reported.\nPhotos and video show people engaged in an intense vogue battle, turning Old Compton Street into a makeshift runway.\u00a0\nBroadly U.K. editor Zing Tsjeng aptly described the spectacle\u00a0as \"solidarity through dance.\"Various public figures, including Labour Party leader Jeremy Corbyn, London Mayor Sadiq Khan and actor Andrew Garfield, were spotted at the event.\u00a0\nThe tragedy in Orlando was the worst mass shooting in U.S. history. Authorities are trying to piece together what motived the shooter, Omar Mateen, to target the LGBTQ community and pledge solidarity to the self-described Islamic State militant group.\nHow to help:", "title": "Orlando Shooting Vigil In London Turns Into Epic Vogue Battle"}